Package stocker.controller

Class StockerDataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • stocker.controller.StockerDataManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPushReceiver
    public class StockerDataManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements IPushReceiver
    Handles all the communication with the data provider. Can logically be viewed as a part of the controller or, depending on the point of view, as a part of the model of the application.
    Author:
    Marc S. Schneider

      • pushMessageIncoming

        public void pushMessageIncoming​(java.lang.String message)
        Receives and parses a push message from a websocket client and notifies all registered listeners (of type Watchlist or StockerChart) of the change. The listeners are informed no matter whether this information concerns them or not (i.e. they have to check on their side whether they are acutally interested in messages for the symbol that this message refers to).
        Specified by:
        pushMessageIncoming in interface IPushReceiver
        Parameters:
        message - the received message

      • websocketConnectionClosedWithError

        Specified by:
        websocketConnectionClosedWithError in interface IPushReceiver

      • switchDataProvider

        public void switchDataProvider()
        Switch the active data provider to that which is currently set as active in the control's properties. The switch is actually done by setting the new active data provider in the properties; this method only makes sure that the change takes effect and that the push subscriptions are moved to the new provider. Tell all listening watchlists and charts to pull new data; unsubscribe from the old provider, end push connection, create new connection, subscribe to the new provider.

      • getPlotData
